ValueMeaning.preferredName: Congenital Abnormalities of Erythrocyte Differentiation or Function
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Inherited disorders involving abnormalities of red blood cell function, structure, or production.  Some diseases in this group may be associated with bone marrow failure, neutropenia, and/or thrombocytopenia.

Concepts.longName: Congenital Abnormalities of Erythrocyte Differentiation or Function
Concepts.definition: Inherited disorders involving abnormalities of red blood cell function, structure, or production. Some diseases in this group may be associated with bone marrow failure, neutropenia, and/or thrombocytopenia.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A group of rare inherited platelet disorders that involve abnormalities of platelet function or platelet production and that usually cause moderate to severe bleeding problems.

Concepts.definition: A group of rare inherited platelet disorders that involve abnormalities of platelet function or platelet production and that usually cause moderate to severe bleeding problems.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Errors in metabolic processes resulting from inborn genetic mutations that are inherited or acquired in utero.

Concepts.definition: A group of disorders present at birth that involve genetic defects leading to disturbances in carbohydrate, lipid, lysosomal storage or amino acid metabolism in the body.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Life-threatening anemia associated with a high risk of infection or bleeding.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An inherited deficiency of coagulation factor VIII characterized by the tendency to spontaneous or exaggerated post-traumatic hemorrhage.
